    {
      "id": "sybil_14_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_14",
      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies and a 8,000 RPM redline. This example is mechanically robust, with the critical rod bearing service and rear subframe reinforcement already completed to ensure structural rigidity under high torque loads. Power is delivered through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a variable M differential lock, providing exceptional traction and corner-exit speeds. The chassis has been enhanced with a Bilstein PSS10 coilover system for improved damping control and reduced body roll. While the interior and exterior exhibit minor patina consistent with enthusiastic use, the powertrain and drivetrain remain in peak operating condition, making this an ideal specimen for the purist seeking analog feedback and mechanical transparency.",
